org.teatrove.trove.util
Class PropertyMap

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractMap
      org.teatrove.trove.util.PropertyMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
Map
public class PropertyMap
extends AbstractMap

A class that is similar to Properties but preserves original property order and supports a special subMap(java.lang.String) view operation. PropertyMap also has more convenience methods for getting properties as certain types.

Author:
Brian S O'Neill

subMap

public PropertyMap subMap(String key)
Returns a view of this map for keys that are the same as the given key, or start with it (and a separator). The names of the keys in the sub-map have their prefix truncated.

A sub-map of 

 "x" = "a"
 "foo" = "b"
 "foo." = "c"
 "foo.bar" = "d"
 "foo.bar.splat" = "e"
 "foo..bar" = "f"
 ".foo" = "g"
 "" = "h"
 null = "i"
using a key of "foo" results in 
 null = "b"
 "" = "c"
 "bar" = "d"
 "bar.splat" = "e"
 ".bar" = "f"
using a key of "x" results in 
 null = "a"
using a key of "" results in 
 "foo" = "g"
 null = "h"
and using a key of null results in the original map.

subMapKeySet

public void putDefaults(Map map)
